3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour using an 8-hour TWAP of the premium between perpetual and mark prices. The on-chain order book ensures transparent price discovery, while sub-second finality enables rapid position adjustments. Funding payments occur automatically in USDC, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to 0.05% per hour during normal market conditions."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","OP","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OP exhibits higher funding volatility compared to major cryptocurrencies due to its smaller market cap and correlation with L2 development cycles. The frequent 1-hour intervals on Hyperliquid create more arbitrage opportunities when OP funding rates diverge significantly from other exchanges that use 8-hour intervals."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OP funding rates on Hyperliquid typically range from -2% to 8% annually during normal conditions, with extreme spikes during major Optimism announcements. The token shows pronounced positive funding during L2 narrative cycles and negative rates during broader market downturns. Weekly patterns often emerge around Optimism governance proposals and major protocol upgrades. The 1-hour interval structure creates more granular rate adjustments compared to traditional 8-hour cycles."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's 1-hour funding intervals create frequent arbitrage windows when OP rates diverge from Binance, OKX, or Bybit. Cross-exchange spreads often exceed 5% annually during high volatility periods. The on-chain nature eliminates counterparty risk while maintaining competitive rates. Automated strategies can capitalize on rate discrepancies by longing on negative funding exchanges and shorting on positive funding platforms."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OP's correlation with Ethereum and general L2 sentiment creates additional basis risk in funding arbitrage strategies. Hyperliquid's newer ecosystem means lower liquidity during extreme market conditions. USDC-only settlements require careful consideration of stablecoin depeg risks. The single-chain architecture creates concentration risk compared to multi-chain alternatives. Position sizing should account for OP's higher volatility relative to major cryptocurrencies."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are OP funding rates calculated on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and paid every hour on Hyperliquid. This creates 24 funding payments per day, compared to 3 payments on most centralized exchanges, offering more frequent arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"What causes OP funding rates to spike on Hyperliquid?","answer":"OP funding rates typically spike during Optimism ecosystem announcements, major protocol integrations, or broader L2 narrative cycles. The smaller market cap makes OP more sensitive to sentiment shifts than larger cryptocurrencies."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage OP funding rates between Hyperliquid and CEX platforms?","answer":"Yes, funding rate arbitrage between Hyperliquid and centralized exchanges is common. The 1-hour vs 8-hour interval difference creates regular opportunities, especially during volatile periods when rates diverge significantly."},{"question":"What are the main risks of trading OP perpetuals on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Key risks include OP's higher volatility, potential liquidity constraints during extreme moves, USDC settlement exposure, and the platform's newer track record. The on-chain nature eliminates counterparty risk but requires careful gas management."}]}]
